Modem: 
Short for "Modulator Demodulator", the modem is responsible for taking ISP provided analog signals that are deliverd through cables, fiber optics, or phone lines and
converting it into digital data that the computer/machine can understand.
Demodulation occurs when data is going from ISP to Device (Turning analog signals into 1s and 0). Modulation would be from the device back to the ISP (Turning 1s and 0s back
to analog data).

